  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-DOC-01, replace per-row inline action icons in `ResultCard.tsx` (Preview / AI Summary / Open File / Find Similar) and dialog-toolbar icons in `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` (Open Record / Email / Copy Link / Workspace) with a single `MoreVertical20Regular` button per row, consuming the shared `DocumentRowMenu` component from `@spaarke/ui-components` (task 012). Menu opens Fluent v9 `Menu`; trigger uses `appearance="subtle"`, `size="small"`, and MUST `stopPropagation` so the row's click handler does not fire. Menu order: Preview · AI summary · Open file · Find similar · *divider* · Download · Copy link · Email (single-doc convenience) · Open record · *divider* · Toggle workspace · Pin to top · Rename · Delete. **`AiSummaryPopover` on the sparkle icon is RETAINED** (hover quick-glance) AND added to the menu (keyboard access) — both coexist. Every action previously reachable via inline card icon or `FilePreviewDialog` toolbar must be reachable via the 3-dot menu; no orphaned UI affordances.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer expert in Fluent UI v9 `Menu` portal behavior, React 16/17 event propagation, and the Semantic Search PCF architecture (`ResultCard.tsx`, `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`, `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`). Familiar with `@spaarke/ui-components` `DocumentRowMenu` contract (`IDocumentRowMenuTarget`, `DocumentRowAction`) shipped in task 012.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ResultCard.tsx` and `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` consume the shared `DocumentRowMenu` from `@spaarke/ui-components`. All 13 actions wire to existing handlers in `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` (no orphaned affordances). `AiSummaryPopover` hover behavior preserved on sparkle icon. Trigger `stopPropagation` verified — clicking the menu trigger does NOT fire the row click → preview Dialog. PCF builds clean (`npm run build:prod`). Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DOC-01 consolidates 8+ existing actions into a single 13-item menu to clean up the row UI ahead of FR-DOC-04 (list view with column-header row + selection checkbox + Modified columns) and FR-DOC-02 (bulk-action bar). The `DocumentRowMenu` shared component (task 012) already encodes the menu structure, `stopPropagation` behavior, and `disabledActions` prop for permission scoping. This task is the **first consumer** — it wires the shared menu into both row and dialog surfaces while preserving the sparkle popover for hover quick-glance.
    </background>
