  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`ResultCard.tsx` renders a single `MoreVertical20Regular` trigger per row (in addition to the sparkle icon for `AiSummaryPopover`); no other inline action icons remain.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Menu order matches FR-DOC-01 exactly: Preview · AI summary · Open file · Find similar · *divider* · Download · Copy link · Email · Open record · *divider* · Toggle workspace · Pin to top · Rename · Delete.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking the trigger button does NOT fire the row click handler (verified via integration test — preview Dialog does not open).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 13 actions invoke existing handlers in `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` (no orphaned actions).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`FilePreviewDialog.tsx` toolbar icons (Open Record / Email / Copy Link / Workspace) replaced with the same `DocumentRowMenu`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`AiSummaryPopover` hover behavior preserved on sparkle icon; menu's "AI summary" item opens the same popover.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF builds clean (`npm run build:prod`); zero hardcoded hex/rgb in touched files (verifiable by grep).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Component renders correctly in `webLightTheme` AND `webDarkTheme`; axe scan zero violations.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` skills pass with no unresolved findings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows task 040 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Three-dot menu renders with 13 actions in correct order">
      <steps>
        <step>Load Matter form with Documents PCF in dev harness.</step>
        <step>Click the `MoreVertical20Regular` trigger on a result row.</step>
        <step>Verify menu opens with 13 items in spec order (Preview · AI summary · Open file · Find similar · divider · Download · Copy link · Email · Open record · divider · Toggle workspace · Pin to top · Rename · Delete).</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Menu renders all 13 items in exact spec order with 2 dividers.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Trigger stopPropagation — row click does not fire">
      <steps>
        <step>Wire a console.log on the row's onClick handler.</step>
        <step>Click the `MoreVertical20Regular` trigger.</step>
        <step>Verify console.log does NOT fire and `FilePreviewDialog` does NOT open.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Menu opens; row click handler suppressed.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="AiSummaryPopover hover preserved">
      <steps>
        <step>Hover the sparkle icon on a result row.</step>
        <step>Verify `AiSummaryPopover` opens with the AI summary content.</step>
        <step>Open the 3-dot menu and click "AI summary".</step>
        <step>Verify the same `AiSummaryPopover` opens.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Both hover and menu-item paths open the same popover.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark mode compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 settings.</step>
        <step>Open menu; verify menu surface, items, dividers, and trigger button use Fluent v9 dark tokens (no white backgrounds, no black text).</step>
        <step>Run axe-core in both themes.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Zero WCAG 2.1 AA violations in either theme; all colors via Fluent v9 semantic tokens.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="FilePreviewDialog header menu replaces toolbar icons">
      <steps>
        <step>Click a row to open `FilePreviewDialog`.</step>
        <step>Verify dialog header shows a single 3-dot menu (no Open Record / Email / Copy Link / Workspace inline icons).</step>
        <step>Open the menu, invoke "Open record" — verify it navigates correctly.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Dialog header has single menu; all toolbar actions reachable via menu.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Dependencies: task 012 MUST be complete first (DocumentRowMenu exported from `@spaarke/ui-components` barrel). The dialog footer Find similar / Close / Open file buttons move to FR-DOC-03 (task 044, dialog restructure) — do NOT touch those here. The sparkle `AiSummaryPopover` is intentionally kept (per Owner Clarifications row 6 in spec.md: "Keep both — hover popover for quick-glance + menu item for keyboard access"). This task is the first of 7 serial Phase 4 PCF tasks (040 → 046) that all touch `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` and friends — parallel-safe is false across the group.
